DPRK bids farewell to late leader Kim Jong-il
2011-12-28 07:29:10 GMT
The Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Wednesday bid final farewell to the nation's late leader Kim Jong-il.A ceremony of bidding last farewell to Kim Jong-il began at the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the official KCNA news agency reported.TV footage also showed columns of troops stood in the snow on the plaza while a limousine carrying a huge portrait of the late leader moved slowly.The late DPRK leader passed away from "great mental and physical strain" at 08:30 am Dec 17 (2330 GMT Friday), on a train during a field guidance tour, according to DPRK media.
